<h1 style="margin:50px 0px;">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>At Grease Monkey Garage, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our customers. This Privacy and General Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information, as well as our general terms and conditions of service.</p>

<h1 style="margin:50px 0px;">Privacy policy</h1>

<h2>1. Collection of Information</h2>
<p>We may collect personal information from you when you use our garage services, make inquiries, or interact with us through our website, email, or other communication channels. This information may include your name, contact details, vehicle information, and any other information you provide to us voluntarily.</p>

<h2>2. Use of Information</h2>
<p>We use the information collected from you to provide and improve our garage services, respond to your inquiries, process transactions, and communicate with you about your vehicle service needs. We may also use your information for marketing purposes, such as sending promotional offers and updates about our services, but you can opt-out of receiving such communications at any time.</p>

<h2>3. Disclosure of Information</h2>
<p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties without your consent. However, we may share your information with trusted service providers who assist us in operating our business, conducting transactions, or servicing your vehicle. We may also disclose your information as required by law or to protect our rights, property, or safety, or that of others.</p>

<h2>4. Security of Information</h2>
<p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.</p>

<h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information stored by us. If you would like to exercise any of these rights or have any questions about our privacy practices, please contact us using the information provided below.</p>


<h1 style="margin:50px 0px;">General Policy</h1>

<h2>1. Vehicle Storage</h2>
<p>While we take all reasonable precautions to ensure the safety and security of vehicles stored at our garage, we are not responsible for any loss, damage, or theft of vehicles or personal belongings left inside vehicles. We recommend that you remove any valuable items from your vehicle before leaving it with us for service.</p>

<h2>2. Vehicle Lock-In</h2>
<p>In the event that a vehicle is inadvertently locked inside our garage outside of regular operating hours, we will make reasonable efforts to rectify the situation as quickly as possible. However, we are not liable for any inconvenience or damages resulting from a lock-in, including but not limited to missed appointments, delayed pick-ups, or additional service charges.</p>

<h2>3. Changes to Policy</h2>
<p>We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy and General Policy at any time without prior notice. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting on our website. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any updates.</p>

<h2>Please don't contact us</h2>
<p>We'd rather not give contact info.</p>
